A trailer doesn't need to spoil every major detail (like "who wins" or whatever) in order to have spoilers.  Now we know the gorilla kid's father comes around to his music, which is a pretty huge spoiler for that character.  What's more is that we can kind of assume that if anyone wins the contest at all, it probably isn't going to be the gorilla kid, since winning the love/respect of his father is now his 'victory', and the movie won't make him the winner of the contest.  Pretty massive spoiler, really.

Music is communication, and in my humble opinion, carried out to one of its highest forms. Some love math because it's an expression of reality and the forces that comprise it, stripped of all but the austere glory of absolute existence.
